@startuml sell-use-case-flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  ArrowColor Black
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFF0
  BorderColor #CCCCAA
}

title Simplified Use Case Flow: Sell Stocks (Application Core Only)

|#LightBlue| Application Service (Orchestrator) |
start
:Receive **Ticker**, **ShareQuantity**, **Price**
(all Value Objects);
note right
  The service receives
  domain types, not primitives.
  How they arrive (REST, CLI…)
  is not our concern here.
end note

:Load **Portfolio** from outbound port;
note right
  ""portfolioPort.getPortfolioById(id)""
  The port is an abstraction —
  we don't care about the
  storage technology.
end note

|#LightGreen| Portfolio (Aggregate Root) |
:portfolio.sell(Ticker, ShareQuantity, Price);

:Validate: quantity **isPositive()**;
if (quantity positive?) then (yes)
else (no)
  #Pink:throw **InvalidQuantityException**;
  stop
endif

:Find **Holding** for the given Ticker;
if (holding exists?) then (yes)
else (no)
  #Pink:throw **HoldingNotFoundException**;
  stop
endif

|#LightYellow| Holding (Entity) |
:holding.sell(ShareQuantity, Price);

:Check: **getTotalShares() ≥ quantity**;
if (enough shares?) then (yes)
else (no)
  #Pink:throw **ConflictQuantityException**;
  stop
endif

:Iterate lots in **FIFO** order (oldest first);

repeat
  |#Wheat| Lot (Entity) |
  :lot.reduce(sharesToSell);
  :lot.calculateCostBasis(sharesToSell) → Money;
  |#LightYellow| Holding (Entity) |
  :Accumulate costBasis;
  :Subtract sold shares from remainingToSell;
repeat while (remainingToSell > 0?) is (yes)
->no;

:Remove depleted lots (isEmpty());
:Calculate **proceeds** = price × quantity;
:Create **SellResult**(proceeds, costBasis);
note right
  ""profit = proceeds − costBasis""
  Calculated automatically
  inside the Value Object.
end note

|#LightGreen| Portfolio (Aggregate Root) |
:Update **balance** += proceeds;
:Return **SellResult**;

|#LightBlue| Application Service (Orchestrator) |
:Save Portfolio through outbound port;
:Return **SellResult**;
stop

@enduml
